`TransitionSpec.julian0` in the given year.\n\n`n`: zero-based day 0–365. Feb 29 is counted normally in leap years.\n","docLink":"./Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.html#Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayJulian0","kind":"def","line":81,"name":"Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayJulian0","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.lean#L81-L88"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.html#Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayJulian\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Time</span>.<span class=\"name\">TimeZone</span>.<span class=\"name\">TransitionSpec</span>.<span class=\"name\">toEpochDayJulian</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">year</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Year.html#Std.Time.Year.Offset\">Year.Offset</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">day</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Internal/Bounded.html#Std.Time.Internal.Bounded.LE\">Internal.Bounded.LE</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <span class=\"fn\">365</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Day.html#Std.Time.Day.Offset\">Day.Offset</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the `Day.Offset` (days since epoch) for a `TransitionSpec.julian` in the given year.\n\n`Jn`: Julian day 1–365. Feb 29 is never counted, so in a leap year days ≥ 60 are shifted by one.\n","docLink":"./Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.html#Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayJulian","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayJulian","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.lean#L71-L79"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.html#Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayMWD\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Time</span>.<span class=\"name\">TimeZone</span>.<span class=\"name\">TransitionSpec</span>.<span class=\"name\">toEpochDayMWD</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">year</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Year.html#Std.Time.Year.Offset\">Year.Offset</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">month</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Month.html#Std.Time.Month.Ordinal\">Month.Ordinal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">week</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Week.html#Std.Time.Week.Aligned.Ordinal\">Week.Aligned.Ordinal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">day</span> : <a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Weekday.html#Std.Time.Weekday.Ordinal\">Weekday.Ordinal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Std/Time/Date/Unit/Day.html#Std.Time.Day.Offset\">Day.Offset</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the `Day.Offset` (days since epoch) for a `TransitionSpec.mwd` in the given year.\n\n`Mm.w.d`: month `m`, week `w` (1–5; 5 = last), ISO weekday `d` (1 = Monday, 7 = Sunday).\nFinds the `w`-th occurrence of weekday `d` in month `m`; if `w = 5`, returns the last occurrence.\n","docLink":"./Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.html#Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayMWD","kind":"def","line":47,"name":"Std.Time.TimeZone.TransitionSpec.toEpochDayMWD","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Std/Time/Zoned/RecurringRule.lean#L47-L69"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\"